## CLI flags

    toroidzip encode [--reanchor-interval N] [--drift-mode A|B|C] <input.f64> <output.tzrz>
    toroidzip decode <input.tzrz> <output.f64>

`--reanchor-interval N` (default 256): lower = more accurate reconstruction,
larger file. Higher = smaller file, more cumulative float drift between anchors.

`--drift-mode A|B|C` (default A): error-management strategy.
  A = reanchor: periodic verbatim anchors, lossless.
  B = compensate: Kahan log-space product, near-lossless, no size overhead.
  C = quantize: ratios rounded to float32, lossy, more compressible.

